authorizeMaintener(uint256,address).details: Function to authorize an address to maintain a token.

authorizeTokenizer(address).details: Function to authorize an address to create a token.

balanceOf(address,uint256).details: Get the specified address' balance for token with specified ID. Attempting to query the zero account for a balance will result in a revert.

params.account: The address of the token holder

returns._0: The account's balance of the token type requested

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: Get the balance of multiple account/token pairs. If any of the query accounts is the zero account, this query will revert.

params.accounts: The addresses of the token holders

returns._0: Balances for each account and token id pair

createToken(address,uint256,uint256,uint.details: Function to mint an amount of a token with the given ID.

params.feesRecipients: list of addresses receiving transfer fees
params.feesRecipientsPercentage: list of percentage, each one for the corresponding feesRecipients
params.id: ID of the token to be minted
params.minHoldingForCallback: minimum holding to propose a callback
params.recipient: The address that will own the minted tokens
params.supply: Amount of the token to be minted
params.transactionFees: transaction fees: [lumpSumFees (in WEI), valueProportionalFees (ratio of transfered amount * 10**8), storageFees (in storageCredit * 10**8)]

params.ids: list of IDs of the tokens to be minted

deposit(address).details: Function to make an ETH deposit that can be used to pay token transfer .

executeCallback(uint256,uint256).details: Accept a callback. Caller need to recall the function to continue the callback until completed.

returns._0: True if the operator is approved, false if not

isLockedAddress(address).details: Function to check if an address is lockec.

isLockedToken(uint256).details: Function to check if a token is locked.

isMaintener(uint256,address).details: Function to check if an address is authorized to maintain a token.

isTokenizer(address).details: Function to check if an address is authorized to create a token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proposeCallback(uint256,uint256,address[.details: Propose to buy the whole supply of a token. The proposer must hold minHoldingForCallback% of the total supply. StashBlox must approve the price with acceptCallback();

params.callees: list of calless. Empty list means all holders.

refuseCallback(uint256).details: Refuse a callback if the price is not enough.

revokeMaintener(uint256,address).details: Function to revoke the authorization to maintain a token.

revokeTokenizer(address).details: Function to revoke the authorization to create a token.

safeBatchTransferFrom(address,address,ui.details: Transfers `values` amount(s) of `ids` from the `from` address to the `to` address specified. Caller must be approved to manage the tokens being transferred out of the `from` account. If `to` is a smart contract, will call `onERC1155BatchReceived` on `to` and act appropriately.

params.data: Data forwarded to `onERC1155Received` if `to` is a contract receiver

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Transfers `value` amount of an `id` from the `from` address to the `to` address specified. Caller must be approved to manage the tokens being transferred out of the `from` account. If `to` is a smart contract, will call `onERC1155Received` on `to` and act appropriately.

params.data: Data forwarded to `onERC1155Received` if `to` is a contract receiver

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Sets or unsets the approval of a given operator. An operator is allowed to transfer all tokens of the sender on their behalf. Because an account already has operator privileges for itself, this function will revert if the account attempts to set the approval status for itself.

params.approved: representing the status of the approval to be set

setProxyRegistryAddress(address[]).details: Function to update the operator whitelist

setTokenTemplate(uint256,address,uint256.details: Function to create or update a token template for batch creation.

params.feesRecipients: list of addresses receiving transfer fees
params.feesRecipientsPercentage: list of percentage, each one for the corresponding feesRecipients
params.minHoldingForCallback: minimum holding to propose a callback
params.recipient: The address that will own the minted tokens
params.supply: Amount of the token to be minted

params._interfaceID: The interface identifier, as specified in ERC-165

transactionFees(address,uint256,uint256).details: Function to get the transaction price to transfer tokens.

params.account: the address from where to transfer the tokens

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateFeesRecipients(uint256,address[],u.details: Function to update the minimum holding to propose a callback.

params.newFeesRecipients: list of addresses receiving transfer fees
params.newFeesRecipientsPercentage: list of percentage, each one for the corresponding feesRecipients

updateMetadataHash(uint256,uint256).details: Function to update the metadata hash of a token.

updateMinHoldingForCallback(uint256,uint.details: Function to update the minimum holding to propose a callback.

updateStorageCreditPrice(uint256).details: Function to update the price of one "storage credit".

params.newFees: The new transaction fees: [lumpSumFees (in WEI), valueProportionalFees (ratio of transfered amount * 10**8), storageFees (in storageCredit * 10**8)]

withdraw(address,uint256).details: Function to withdraw ETH from the contract.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).notice: Queries the approval status of an operator for a given account.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Query if a contract implements an interface
